ADDITIONAL NOTICE — HEALTHCARE DATA

This software is intended to assist with the anonymisation of NHS patient data
for the purpose of integration testing and development. It is provided as a
tool to support compliance with the UK General Data Protection Regulation
(UK GDPR), the Data Protection Act 2018, and NHS Data Security and Protection
Toolkit (DSPT) obligations.

However, this software does not guarantee complete anonymisation or
de-identification of any data processed through it. Users remain solely
responsible for:

  1. Ensuring that the use of this software complies with their organisation's
     data protection policies, information governance frameworks, and any
     applicable legal obligations.

  2. Verifying that all output produced by this software is free of patient-
     identifiable information before use in any non-secure environment.

  3. Ensuring that real patient data is not stored, shared, or transmitted in
     an unsecured manner during or after processing.

  4. Obtaining appropriate data protection impact assessments (DPIAs) where
     required by their organisation or by law.

The authors and contributors of this software accept no liability for any
breach of data protection law, loss of data, or harm arising from the use or
misuse of this software.

